**why —** The arithmetic completed: alone with one, then two, then the many — and at the last, when the many become One, there is no one left to be alone. The deepest solitude is the end of the self.

**how —** Crystallized from the philosophy, religion, and science of dissolution into the whole.

**◌ the mythos —** The arithmetic completed: alone with one, then two, then the many — and at the last, when the many become One, there is no one left to be alone. The deepest solitude is the end of the self. the many become One, and no one left to be alone

